<br>
<br>
It's been my experience that the only real thing a wizard can bring to any group or raid setting is burst dps. But the basic limitations of agro present for all classes seem to keep me from really doing more burst dps than just about any nuker. At least enough so to be truly noticeable. Though it is noticeable when i get beat on.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, i was thinking a spell similar to Yaulp which would be a shortlived 4-5tick buff that while on you, would reduce any further spells cast to a manaburn-like 1pt of agro.<br>
<br>
It would take up a spell slot to use, like clr yaulp would wear off if you sat, but would give you a chance to chain cast some high dps nukes like SoS. Manacost would preclude doing this always of course. But we could pull this off in 'special' cases.<br>
<br>
If we could chain some SoS here and there our burst DPS would truly be noted in situations. Even in situations where mt died and group-wipe was imminent this would enable us to put the hurt on potientially saving the day. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 13046<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 9:33 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yaulp for wizzies (just an idea)</span><hr size=1> Not a bad idea.<br>
